Lan Airlines Raises Price for International Fares on Fuel Costs

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-02-25T21:47:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/lan-airlines-raises-price-for-international-fares-on-fuel-costs.html
  Lan Airlines SA , Latin America’s
largest airline by market value, will increase fares for
international flights to blunt higher fuel costs.  Lan will raise fares for international routes by 8 percent
to 12 percent, according to an e-mailed statement.  Oil prices in  New York  surged to a 29-month high yesterday
amid concern that  Libya ’s crude output was cut by as much as
two-thirds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
